cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.IR, cs.CL

The paper analyzes social media activity related to a sports event, which falls under the category of social media analysis. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves text analysis, which could fall under cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) or cs.CL (Computation and Language). The analysis of geo-tagged data could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
